			<div class="content" id="post-content-4665987">
									

<p>I’m very torn on this piece.</p>
<p>The last two bits are phenomenal, especially the script-like section at the very end. However everything up until the Fungus entity is a bit of a slog to get through and I struggle taking it wholly seriously.</p>
<p>The Administrator as a character also lacks a cohesive voice throughout the story IMO. He comes off <em>way</em> more self-serious in the first sections before becoming a lot more fun towards the end. The last part reminded me a lot of David Tennant’s 10th Doctor in the best way possible.</p>
<p>I’m going to novote on this one. It’s got some awesome parts but the opening chapters make it hard for me to upvote.</p>

							</div>

								
					
